---
id: org.dxos.plugin.discord
name: DiscordPlugin
version: 0.1.0
---

A Composer plugin that configures and controls a Discord bot. The bot runs as a
Cloudflare Worker, receives Discord slash commands, and communicates with DXOS
EDGE. The plugin stores bot identity and configuration as ECHO objects in the
space — the bot's credentials, guild bindings, and channel mappings are all
first-class replicated data.

Two packages:
- `packages/plugins/plugin-discord` — Composer plugin (types, surfaces, operations).
- `packages/experimental/discord-worker` — Cloudflare Worker (slash command handler).

## Extensions

The following extension dialects are used in this document.
Each extension is defined in the Appendix or resolved via its URI.

| Term        | URI                            |
|-------------|--------------------------------|
| `type`      | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`       |
| `feat`      | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`       |
| `test`      | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`       |
| `component` | `org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0`  |
| `op`        | `org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0`         |
| `service`   | `org.dxos.mdl.service@1.0`    |

## Types

```mdl
type BotStatus
  literals: disconnected | connected | error
```

```mdl
type ChannelBinding
  desc: A Discord channel mapped to the current space.
  fields:
    channelId: string
    channelName: string
```

```mdl
type Bot
  desc: >
    Core ECHO object representing a Discord bot instance.
    Stores identity, credentials, and guild binding.
    NOTE: In the current phase the HALO keypair lives directly in this object.
    A future phase will promote the bot to its own ECHO identity.
  fields:
    name: string
    token?: string                # Discord bot token (encrypted in space)
    applicationId?: string        # Discord application ID
    did?: string                  # Bot DID derived from HALO keypair
    publicKey?: string            # HALO public key (hex)
    privateKey?: string           # HALO private key (hex)
    guildId?: string              # Connected Discord guild ID
    guildName?: string            # Connected guild display name
    channels: ChannelBinding[]    # Tracked channels
    status: BotStatus             # Connection state
    inviteUrl?: string            # OAuth URL for adding bot to guild
```

## Components

```mdl
component BotArticle
  desc: >
    Configuration article surface bound to a Bot object.
    Displays bot identity, connection status, and guild binding.
    Initial version is minimal — read-only display with setup actions.
  props:
    bot: Bot
  state:
    tokenVisible: boolean         # Toggle masked/unmasked token display
  slots:
    header?: ReactNode
    actions?: ReactNode           # Slot for future admin actions
  actions:
    copyInviteUrl()               # Copy OAuth invite URL to clipboard
    disconnect()                  # Remove guild binding
    setToken(token: string)       # Paste-to-set bot token
    setApplicationId(id: string)  # Set Discord application ID
  emits:
    onDisconnect()
  layout: |
    ┌─────────────────────────────────┐
    │ [header slot]                   │
    ├─────────────────────────────────┤
    │ Status: ● connected             │
    │ Name:   my-bot                  │
    ├─────────────────────────────────┤
    │ Application ID  [__________]    │
    │ Bot Token       [••••••••] 👁   │
    ├─────────────────────────────────┤
    │ Invite URL      [Copy]          │
    ├─────────────────────────────────┤
    │ Guild: My Server                │
    │ Channels:                       │
    │   #general                      │
    │   #bugs                         │
    ├─────────────────────────────────┤
    │ [actions slot]                  │
    │ [Disconnect]                    │
    └─────────────────────────────────┘
```

## Services

```mdl
service EdgeGateway
  desc: >
    DXOS EDGE endpoint that receives requests from the Cloudflare Worker.
    Validates bot DID membership and routes commands to the appropriate space.
  ops:
    connect(did: string, guildId: string, guildName: string, channelId: string, spaceKey: string) → void
    track(did: string, spaceKey: string, markdown: string, threadName: string) → void
  errors:
    Unauthorized: DID is not a member of the target space
    SpaceNotFound: space key does not match any known space
```

```mdl
service DiscordApi
  desc: Discord REST API used by the Worker to fetch thread messages.
  loading: lazy
  ops:
    getThreadMessages(channelId: string, botToken: string) → Message[]
  errors:
    Forbidden: bot lacks permissions to read the channel
    NotFound: channel does not exist
```

## Operations

```mdl
op createBot
  desc: Creates a new Bot object with a generated HALO keypair and stores it in the space.
  input:
    name: string
    applicationId?: string
  output: Bot
  effects: [echo:write]
  note: >
    Generates a HALO keypair using the DXOS client available in the plugin context.
    Derives the DID from the public key. Constructs the OAuth invite URL from
    the application ID with pre-configured scopes (bot, applications.commands).
```

```mdl
op setToken
  desc: Sets the Discord bot token on an existing Bot object.
  input:
    bot: Bot
    token: string
  output: Bot
  effects: [echo:write]
  note: Token is stored encrypted in the space via ECHO.
```

```mdl
op connectGuild
  desc: >
    Called when the /connect slash command completes successfully.
    Updates the Bot object with guild info and channel binding.
  input:
    bot: Bot
    guildId: string
    guildName: string
    channelId: string
    channelName: string
  output: Bot
  effects: [echo:write]
  note: >
    Triggered by EDGE after the Worker forwards the /connect interaction.
    Adds the guild binding and initial channel to the Bot object.
```

```mdl
op disconnectGuild
  desc: Removes guild binding from the Bot object.
  input:
    bot: Bot
  output: Bot
  effects: [echo:write]
  note: Clears guildId, guildName, channels. Sets status to disconnected.
```

```mdl
op trackThread
  desc: >
    Called when the /track slash command completes.
    Creates a Markdown document in the space from a Discord thread transcript.
  input:
    spaceKey: string
    threadName: string
    markdown: string
  output: Document
  effects: [echo:write]
  note: >
    Creates a new Markdown document with the thread content.
    Placeholder for future agent behavior — initially just a raw transcript.
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Bot Creation

  req F-1.1: User can create a Bot object from Composer via blueprint.
  req F-1.2: HALO keypair generated and stored in Bot on creation.
  req F-1.3: DID derived from public key and stored in Bot.
  req F-1.4: Bot created with status disconnected.
```

```mdl
feat F-2: Bot Configuration

  req F-2.1: User can set the Discord bot token via the BotArticle surface.
  req F-2.2: User can set the Discord application ID.
  req F-2.3: Invite URL auto-generated from application ID with scopes: bot, applications.commands.
  req F-2.4: Invite URL can be copied to clipboard.
  req F-2.5: Bot token displayed masked by default, toggleable.
```

```mdl
feat F-3: Guild Connection (/connect)

  req F-3.1: Discord /connect slash command registered with the Worker.
  req F-3.2:
    when: user invokes /connect <space-key> in Discord
    then: Worker forwards to EDGE with bot DID
  req F-3.3:
    when: EDGE validates DID membership
    then: Bot object updated with guild and channel info
  req F-3.4:
    when: connection succeeds
    then: Bot.status set to connected; ephemeral Discord confirmation sent
  req F-3.5:
    when: EDGE rejects the DID
    then: ephemeral Discord error sent; Bot unchanged
```

```mdl
feat F-4: Thread Tracking (/track)

  req F-4.1: Discord /track slash command registered with the Worker.
  req F-4.2:
    when: user invokes /track in a Discord thread
    then: Worker fetches all messages in the thread
  req F-4.3:
    when: messages fetched
    then: formatted as Markdown (author, timestamp, content per message)
  req F-4.4:
    when: Markdown ready
    then: Worker POSTs to EDGE; new Markdown document created in space
  req F-4.5:
    when: document created
    then: ephemeral Discord confirmation with document reference
```

```mdl
feat F-5: Configuration Surface

  req F-5.1: BotArticle rendered as article surface when Bot object selected.
  req F-5.2: Shows bot name, status indicator, application ID, masked token.
  req F-5.3: Shows connected guild name and tracked channels when connected.
  req F-5.4: Disconnect button removes guild binding.
  req F-5.5: Copy button for invite URL.
```

```mdl
feat F-6: Worker (discord-worker)

  req F-6.1: Cloudflare Worker receives Discord interaction webhooks.
  req F-6.2: Verifies Discord request signatures.
  req F-6.3: Routes /connect and /track to appropriate handlers.
  req F-6.4: Stateless — all persistent state lives in the space.
  req F-6.5: Bot token stored as Cloudflare Worker secret for Discord API calls.
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: Create bot with keypair
  given: user is in a space in Composer
  when: user creates a Discord Bot via blueprint
  then:
    - Bot object created in space
    - Bot.did is a valid DID string
    - Bot.publicKey and Bot.privateKey are set
    - Bot.status === disconnected
    - Bot.channels is empty
```

```mdl
test T-2: Set bot token
  given: a Bot object exists in the space
  when: user pastes a bot token in the BotArticle
  then:
    - Bot.token is set
    - Token displays masked in the UI
```

```mdl
test T-3: Generate invite URL
  given: a Bot with applicationId set
  when: BotArticle renders
  then:
    - Invite URL contains the application ID
    - URL includes scopes: bot, applications.commands
    - Copy button copies URL to clipboard
```

```mdl
test T-4: Connect guild via slash command
  given: a Bot exists with valid DID, Worker is deployed
  when: user runs /connect <space-key> in Discord
  then:
    - Worker POSTs to EDGE with DID and guild info
    - Bot.guildId and Bot.guildName populated
    - Bot.status === connected
    - Ephemeral Discord message confirms connection
```

```mdl
test T-5: Reject unauthorized connect
  given: a Bot whose DID is not a member of the target space
  when: /connect <space-key> invoked
  then:
    - EDGE returns Unauthorized
    - Ephemeral Discord error message shown
    - Bot object unchanged
```

```mdl
test T-6: Track thread creates document
  given: a connected Bot, user is in a Discord thread with 5 messages
  when: user runs /track
  then:
    - Worker fetches 5 thread messages
    - Markdown document created in space
    - Document contains all 5 messages with author and timestamp
    - Ephemeral Discord confirmation sent
```

```mdl
test T-7: Disconnect guild
  given: a Bot with status connected and a guild binding
  when: user clicks Disconnect in BotArticle
  then:
    - Bot.guildId and Bot.guildName cleared
    - Bot.channels emptied
    - Bot.status === disconnected
```

```mdl
test T-8: BotArticle displays configuration
  given: a Bot with token, applicationId, and connected guild
  when: BotArticle renders
  then:
    - Status indicator shows connected
    - Token displayed as masked (••••)
    - Guild name visible
    - Channel list visible
    - Disconnect button enabled
```

---

## Design Notes

### Authentication Model

The initial authentication model is stateless DID-in-header (approach 3):
- Worker includes the bot DID in requests to EDGE.
- EDGE validates that the DID is a member of the target space.
- No request signing in this phase.

**Future iteration:** Add HALO request signing. The Worker signs each request
with the bot's private key (stored as a Cloudflare secret). EDGE verifies
the signature against the DID's public key.

### Bot Identity Evolution

Current phase: Bot's HALO keypair (publicKey, privateKey) stored directly in
the Bot config object. The bot does not have a full ECHO identity.

Future phase: Bot promoted to its own ECHO identity with full HALO credentials.
The Bot type schema is designed so this migration is additive — the keypair
fields become redundant but don't break.

### Worker Configuration

The Worker requires two secrets:
- `DISCORD_PUBLIC_KEY` — for verifying Discord interaction signatures.
- `BOT_TOKEN` — for Discord API calls (fetching thread messages).

**Future iteration:** Worker fetches its own config from the space via EDGE,
eliminating the need for env-var configuration. The bot authenticates to EDGE
with its DID, pulls its token and other config from the Bot ECHO object.

### Relationship to existing discord-bot

The `packages/experimental/discord-bot` package is superseded by this design.
Useful code (Discord.js patterns, message fetching) should be absorbed into
`discord-worker`. The experimental package can be deleted once the Worker is
functional.

---

## Appendix: Extension Definitions

Extension block types used in this document are defined below using
the core `ext` primitive — the only construct the base language provides.

```mdl
ext type
  uri: dxos.spec/ext/type@1.0
  desc: A named data structure with typed fields and optional literals.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    fields?: FieldMap        # name[?]: TypeExpr  (# inline comment)
    literals?: UnionList     # a | b | c
    extends?: TypeRef[]
```

```mdl
ext feat
  uri: dxos.spec/ext/feat@1.0
  desc: A named feature grouping one or more requirements.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    req: RequirementList
  nesting: self              # feat blocks may contain feat blocks
```

```mdl
ext test
  uri: dxos.spec/ext/test@1.0
  desc: An acceptance scenario expressed as given / when / then steps.
  fields:
    given?: Step | Step[]
    when?: Step | Step[]
    then: Step | Step[]
    tags?: TagList
```

```mdl
ext component
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0
  desc: A UI component with props, internal state, slots, actions, and events.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    props?: FieldMap            # external inputs (immutable inside component)
    state?: FieldMap            # internal reactive state
    slots?: FieldMap            # named ReactNode injection points
    actions?: ActionMap         # methods the component exposes or handles
    emits?: EventMap            # events the component raises to its parent
    layout?: CodeBlock          # ASCII sketch of visual structure (non-normative)
```

```mdl
ext op
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0
  desc: |
    A named operation with typed inputs, outputs, and declared errors.
    Pure ops have no effects or requires. Effectful ops declare both.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    input?: FieldMap            # named input parameters
    output?: TypeExpr           # return type
    errors?: ErrorMap           # name: Prose  (when this error occurs)
    effects?: EffectList        # echo:read | echo:write | http | fs | ...
    requires?: ServiceList      # injected service dependencies
    note?: Prose                # implementation guidance (non-normative)
```

```mdl
ext service
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.service@1.0
  desc: An external or system-level dependency providing named operations.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    loading?: eager | lazy
    ops?: OpMap                 # name(params) → ReturnType
    errors?: ErrorMap
    note?: Prose
```
